Payroll Data Analysis¶

🔹 Objective:¶

This analysis explores payroll data to find key insights, such as:

  • Department-wise salary distribution
  • Trends in payroll over time
  • Outliers in salary payments

🔹 Dataset Overview:¶

The dataset contains payroll records, including:

  • PayPeriodEndDate: The date when salary was processed
  • BasicPay: The base salary of employees
  • Department: The department of the employee

🔹 Tools Used:¶

  • Python (pandas, seaborn, matplotlib)
  • SQL Server (pyodbc)

Key Insights from Payroll Data¶

1️⃣ Department-wise Salaries:

  • The highest payroll spending is in the IT department.
  • The HR department has the lowest total payroll.

2️⃣ Payroll Trends Over Time:

  • Salaries have shown an upward trend in Q4, likely due to bonuses.
  • There was a sudden spike in March, which could be a payroll correction.

3️⃣ Outliers in Salary Distribution:

  • We detected high salaries in the Executive team, which may be due to leadership bonuses.

🔹 Recommendations:¶

  • Investigate the March payroll spike to confirm if it's a one-time event or a system issue.
  • Consider redistributing HR department salaries for better pay equity.
